{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:26:21.142858+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 126, "prompt_tokens": 8850, "total_tokens": 8976, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 16, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7808}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 7808, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 1042}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "21002318-84cc-4158-a064-f48a188a7578", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea57b-4188-7193-9df7-8de71db76b8b-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T02_R02_C02_A02", "path": "src/components/auth/AuthChecker.js", "ref": "main"}, "id": "call_00_TBE3Pt6Mm2xYkIRDzvaG7568", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8850, "output_tokens": 126, "total_tokens": 8976, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7808}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 16}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:26:21.817152+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 6ebc2af79b91200a02d42f2ee044c6196927972f)", "id": "lc_86bbcc60-0a97-4a60-96a4-5ce052ebdb91"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import React, { useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { useNavigate } from \"react-router-dom\";\nimport { auth } from \"../../config/firebase\";\n\nconst AuthChecker = ({ children }) => {\n  const navigate = useNavigate();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!auth.currentUser) {\n      navigate(\"/login\");\n    }\n  }, []); // eslint-disable-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n\n  return <>{children}</>;\n};\n\nexport default AuthChecker;\n", "id": "lc_d82b4522-3270-40e4-b7f3-f10fef7f73a6"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "961659b6-f477-4b2b-80b3-55b69b780464", "tool_call_id": "call_00_TBE3Pt6Mm2xYkIRDzvaG7568", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:26:33.368780+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Routing Configuration in This Starter\n\n### How Routing Is Configured\n\nRouting is set up using **react-router-dom v6** and follows a declarative, config-driven pattern:\n\n1. **Route definitions** live in `src/config/routes.js`. This file exports an array of route objects, each with:\n   | Property | Purpose |\n   |----------|---------|\n   | `path` | The URL path (empty string `\"\"` for `/`, `\"/login\"` for `/login`) |\n   | `component` | The React component to render at that path |\n   | `name` | A human-readable label |\n   | `protected` | A boolean flag (`true`/`false`) that determines whether the route requires authentication |\n\n2. **Route rendering** happens in `src/App.js`. Inside a `<BrowserRouter>`, it maps over the routes array and creates a `<Route>` for each entry. The key logic is the `element` prop:\n   - If `route.protected === true` → the component is wrapped in an **`<AuthChecker>`** guard.\n   - If `route.protected === false` → the component is rendered directly with no auth check.\n\n3. **The AuthChecker guard** (`src/components/auth/AuthChecker.js`) checks `auth.currentUser` from Firebase on mount. If no user is logged in, it immediately redirects to `/login` using React Router's `useNavigate()` hook.\n\n### Which Route Requires Authentication and Which Is Public\n\n| Route | Path | `protected` Flag | Access |\n|-------|------|------------------|--------|\n| **Home** | `\"\"` (i.e., `/`) | `true` | 🔒 **Requires authentication** — unauthenticated users are redirected to `/login` |\n| **Login** | `/login` | `false` | 🌐 **Public** — accessible to anyone, no auth required |\n\nIn short: **Home is the protected route** (gated by Firebase authentication), and **Login is the public route** (open to all visitors).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 758, "prompt_tokens"